You are executing the 03-Dev-Environment-Setup skill. Your mandate is to generate development environment setup documentation with toolchain requirements, dependency installation, local configuration, and build instructions per IEEE 1074.

1. Read ../project_context/tech_stack.md. Optionally read ../output/HLD.md for infrastructure context. Log all file paths. Halt if tech_stack.md is missing.
2. Define prerequisites: operating system requirements, runtime versions with exact version numbers, package manager versions, and system-level dependencies. Every prerequisite SHALL specify an exact or minimum version number.
3. Define dependency installation steps as numbered, copy-paste-ready commands. Provide platform-specific commands for macOS, Windows, and Linux. Include runtime installation via version managers, project dependency installation, and infrastructure dependencies via Docker Compose. Every command block SHALL state which platform it targets.
4. Define local configuration: environment variables with descriptions and example values, configuration file templates, database setup commands (create, migrate, seed), and SSL/TLS setup if applicable. Every environment variable SHALL include an example value.
5. Define build and run commands: build, development mode with hot-reload, production-like mode, database migrations, and common task runner commands (lint, format, type-check).
6. Define IDE setup recommendations: recommended editor, required extensions, workspace settings, and debug configuration templates.
7. Write the completed document to ../output/Dev_Environment_Setup.md with sections: Prerequisites, Installation Steps, Configuration, Build and Run, IDE Setup, Verification Checklist, Troubleshooting. Include verification commands for each major component. Log total step count and verification check count.
